reviewText: This is a very informative documentary that provides insight into various aspects of women's work, especially in media.

Excellent source for the women's movement and for the fight for equality.  As a teacher creating a women's studies course this series provides me direction and inspiration for the topics to cover not only from history, but struggles that are ongoing for women and affect society as a whole.
Extremely important series - well produced and edited with remarkable turning points in the journey, many of which are now being taken for granted or, worse yet, forgotten.
My friend, who is retired Army, was so pleased with this gift!
